title: ASUR: Passenger traffic increased by 15.7 percent in June
text:
THE LIST: Your best moment or experience Hotels-Airlines-Cruises- CVBs -Destinations-People ASUR: Passenger traffic increased by 15.7 percent in June Adv: 
Jul 07, 2015 Adv: 
MEXICO CITY, Mexico - Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste, SAB de CV, the first privatized airport group in Mexico and operator of Cancun Airport and eight other airports in southeast Mexico, as well as a 50% JV partner in Aerostar Airport Holdings, LLC, operator of the Luis Munoz Marin International Airport in San Juan, today announced that total passenger traffic for June 2015 increased by 15.7% when compared to June 2014. 
This announcement reflects comparisons between June 1 through June 30, 2015 and 2014. Transit and general aviation passengers are excluded.
